definitions.definition: Small non- retractable fins , generally on the caudal peduncle between the last dorsal or anal fin and the caudal fin of some fishes . In some groups, such as tuna , finlets are rayless.

main_definition: ( ichthyology ) Small non- retractable fins , generally on the caudal peduncle between the last dorsal or anal fin and the caudal fin of some fishes . In some groups, such as tuna , finlets are rayless.
